text: Clark Todd Scully (September 13, 1948 - September 6, 2021) was an American racewalker. He competed in the men's 20 kilometres walk at the 1976 Summer Olympics. He was born in Princeton, New Jersey. Scully died on September 6, 2021 in a car crash in Big Island, Virginia at the age of 72. ==References== Category:1948 births Category:2021 deaths Category:American track and field athletes Category:Racewalkers Category:Sportspeople from New Jersey Category:People from Princeton, New Jersey
